41typedef struct dlopen_data {
42 isc_mem_t *mctx;
43 char *dl_path;
44 char *dlzname;
45 void *dl_handle;
46 void *dbdata;
47 unsigned int flags;
48 isc_mutex_t lock;
49 int version;
50 bool in_configure;
51
52 dlz_dlopen_version_t *dlz_version;
53 dlz_dlopen_create_t *dlz_create;
54 dlz_dlopen_findzonedb_t *dlz_findzonedb;
55 dlz_dlopen_lookup_t *dlz_lookup;
56 dlz_dlopen_authority_t *dlz_authority;
57 dlz_dlopen_allnodes_t *dlz_allnodes;
58 dlz_dlopen_allowzonexfr_t *dlz_allowzonexfr;
59 dlz_dlopen_newversion_t *dlz_newversion;
60 dlz_dlopen_closeversion_t *dlz_closeversion;
61 dlz_dlopen_configure_t *dlz_configure;
62 dlz_dlopen_ssumatch_t *dlz_ssumatch;
63 dlz_dlopen_addrdataset_t *dlz_addrdataset;
64 dlz_dlopen_subrdataset_t *dlz_subrdataset;
65 dlz_dlopen_delrdataset_t *dlz_delrdataset;
66 dlz_dlopen_destroy_t *dlz_destroy;
67} dlopen_data_t;
68
69/* Modules can choose whether they are lock-safe or not. */
70#define MAYBE_LOCK(cd) \
71 do { \
72 if ((cd->flags & DNS_SDLZFLAG_THREADSAFE) == 0 && \
73 cd->in_configure == false) \
74 LOCK(&cd->lock); \
75 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
76
77#define MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd) \
78 do { \
79 if ((cd->flags & DNS_SDLZFLAG_THREADSAFE) == 0 && \
80 cd->in_configure == false) \
81 UNLOCK(&cd->lock); \
82 } while (0)
83
84/*
85 * Log a message at the given level.
86 */
87static void dlopen_log(int level, const char *fmt, ...)
88{
89 va_list ap;
90 va_start(ap, fmt);
91 isc_log_vwrite(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
92 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(level),
93 fmt, ap);
94 va_end(ap);
95}

101static isc_result_t
102dlopen_dlz_allnodes(const char *zone, void *driverarg, void *dbdata,
103 dns_sdlzallnodes_t *allnodes)
104{
105 dlopen_data_t *cd = (dlopen_data_t *) dbdata;
106 isc_result_t result;
107
108
109 UNUSED(driverarg);
110
111 if (cd->dlz_allnodes == NULL) {
112 return (ISC_R_NOPERM);
113 }
114
115 MAYBE_LOCK(cd);
116 result = cd->dlz_allnodes(zone, cd->dbdata, allnodes);
117 MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd);
118 return (result);
119}

196/*
197 * Load a symbol from the library
198 */
199static void *
200dl_load_symbol(dlopen_data_t *cd, const char *symbol, bool mandatory) {
201 void *ptr = dlsym(cd->dl_handle, symbol);
202 if (ptr == NULL && mandatory) {
203 dlopen_log(ISC_LOG_ERROR,
204 "dlz_dlopen: library '%s' is missing "
205 "required symbol '%s'", cd->dl_path, symbol);
206 }
207 return (ptr);
208}
209
210/*
211 * Called at startup for each dlopen zone in named.conf
212 */
213static isc_result_t
214dlopen_dlz_create(const char *dlzname, unsigned int argc, char *argv[],
215 void *driverarg, void **dbdata)
216{
217 dlopen_data_t *cd;
218 isc_mem_t *mctx = NULL;
219 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
220 int dlopen_flags = 0;
221
222 UNUSED(driverarg);
223
224 if (argc < 2) {
225 dlopen_log(ISC_LOG_ERROR,
226 "dlz_dlopen driver for '%s' needs a path to "
227 "the shared library", dlzname);
228 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
229 }
230
231 result = isc_mem_create(0, 0, &mctx);
232 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
233 return (result);
234
235 cd = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*cd));
236 if (cd == NULL) {
237 isc_mem_destroy(&mctx);
238 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
239 }
240 memset(cd, 0, sizeof(*cd));
241
242 cd->mctx = mctx;
243
244 cd->dl_path = isc_mem_strdup(cd->mctx, argv[1]);
245 if (cd->dl_path == NULL) {
246 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
247 goto failed;
248 }
249
250 cd->dlzname = isc_mem_strdup(cd->mctx, dlzname);
251 if (cd->dlzname == NULL) {
252 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
253 goto failed;
254 }
255
256 /* Initialize the lock */
257 isc_mutex_init(&cd->lock);
258
259 /* Open the library */
260 dlopen_flags = RTLD_NOW|RTLD_GLOBAL;
261
262#if defined(RTLD_DEEPBIND) && !__SANITIZE_ADDRESS__
263 /*
264 * If RTLD_DEEPBIND is available then use it. This can avoid
265 * issues with a module using a different version of a system
266 * library than one that bind9 uses. For example, bind9 may link
267 * to MIT kerberos, but the module may use Heimdal. If we don't
268 * use RTLD_DEEPBIND then we could end up with Heimdal functions
269 * calling MIT functions, which leads to bizarre results (usually
270 * a segfault).
271 */
272 dlopen_flags |= RTLD_DEEPBIND;
273#endif
274
275 cd->dl_handle = dlopen(cd->dl_path, dlopen_flags);
276 if (cd->dl_handle == NULL) {
277 dlopen_log(ISC_LOG_ERROR,
278 "dlz_dlopen failed to open library '%s' - %s",
279 cd->dl_path, dlerror());
280 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
281 goto failed;
282 }
283
284 /* Find the symbols */
285 cd->dlz_version = (dlz_dlopen_version_t *)
286 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_version", true);
287 cd->dlz_create = (dlz_dlopen_create_t *)
288 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_create", true);
289 cd->dlz_lookup = (dlz_dlopen_lookup_t *)
290 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_lookup", true);
291 cd->dlz_findzonedb = (dlz_dlopen_findzonedb_t *)
292 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_findzonedb", true);
293
294 if (cd->dlz_create == NULL ||
295 cd->dlz_version == NULL ||
296 cd->dlz_lookup == NULL ||
297 cd->dlz_findzonedb == NULL)
298 {
299 /* We're missing a required symbol */
300 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
301 goto failed;
302 }
303
304 cd->dlz_allowzonexfr = (dlz_dlopen_allowzonexfr_t *)
305 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_allowzonexfr", false);
306 cd->dlz_allnodes = (dlz_dlopen_allnodes_t *)
307 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_allnodes",
308 (cd->dlz_allowzonexfr != NULL));
309 cd->dlz_authority = (dlz_dlopen_authority_t *)
310 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_authority", false);
311 cd->dlz_newversion = (dlz_dlopen_newversion_t *)
312 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_newversion", false);
313 cd->dlz_closeversion = (dlz_dlopen_closeversion_t *)
314 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_closeversion",
315 (cd->dlz_newversion != NULL));
316 cd->dlz_configure = (dlz_dlopen_configure_t *)
317 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_configure", false);
318 cd->dlz_ssumatch = (dlz_dlopen_ssumatch_t *)
319 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_ssumatch", false);
320 cd->dlz_addrdataset = (dlz_dlopen_addrdataset_t *)
321 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_addrdataset", false);
322 cd->dlz_subrdataset = (dlz_dlopen_subrdataset_t *)
323 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_subrdataset", false);
324 cd->dlz_delrdataset = (dlz_dlopen_delrdataset_t *)
325 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_delrdataset", false);
326 cd->dlz_destroy = (dlz_dlopen_destroy_t *)
327 dl_load_symbol(cd, "dlz_destroy", false);
328
329 /* Check the version of the API is the same */
330 cd->version = cd->dlz_version(&cd->flags);
331 if (cd->version < (DLZ_DLOPEN_VERSION - DLZ_DLOPEN_AGE) ||
332 cd->version > DLZ_DLOPEN_VERSION)
333 {
334 dlopen_log(ISC_LOG_ERROR,
335 "dlz_dlopen: %s: incorrect driver API version %d, "
336 "requires %d",
337 cd->dl_path, cd->version, DLZ_DLOPEN_VERSION);
338 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
339 goto failed;
340 }
341
342 /*
343 * Call the library's create function. Note that this is an
344 * extended version of dlz create, with the addition of
345 * named function pointers for helper functions that the
346 * driver will need. This avoids the need for the backend to
347 * link the BIND9 libraries
348 */
349 MAYBE_LOCK(cd);
350 result = cd->dlz_create(dlzname, argc-1, argv+1,
351 &cd->dbdata,
352 "log", dlopen_log,
353 "putrr", dns_sdlz_putrr,
354 "putnamedrr", dns_sdlz_putnamedrr,
355 "writeable_zone", dns_dlz_writeablezone,
356 NULL);
357 MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd);
358 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
359 goto failed;
360
361 *dbdata = cd;
362
363 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
364
365failed:
366 dlopen_log(ISC_LOG_ERROR, "dlz_dlopen of '%s' failed", dlzname);
367 if (cd->dl_path != NULL) {
368 isc_mem_free(mctx, cd->dl_path);
369 }
370 if (cd->dlzname != NULL) {
371 isc_mem_free(mctx, cd->dlzname);
372 }
373 if (dlopen_flags != 0) {
374 isc_mutex_destroy(&cd->lock);
375 }
376#ifdef HAVE_DLCLOSE
377 if (cd->dl_handle) {
378 dlclose(cd->dl_handle);
379 }
380#endif
381 isc_mem_put(mctx, cd, sizeof(*cd));
382 isc_mem_destroy(&mctx);
383 return (result);
384}
385
386/*
387 * Called when bind is shutting down
388 */
389static void
390dlopen_dlz_destroy(void *driverarg, void *dbdata) {
391 dlopen_data_t *cd = (dlopen_data_t *) dbdata;
392 isc_mem_t *mctx;
393
394 UNUSED(driverarg);
395
396 if (cd->dlz_destroy) {
397 MAYBE_LOCK(cd);
398 cd->dlz_destroy(cd->dbdata);
399 MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd);
400 }
401
402 if (cd->dl_path) {
403 isc_mem_free(cd->mctx, cd->dl_path);
404 }
405 if (cd->dlzname) {
406 isc_mem_free(cd->mctx, cd->dlzname);
407 }
408
409#ifdef HAVE_DLCLOSE
410 if (cd->dl_handle) {
411 dlclose(cd->dl_handle);
412 }
413#endif
414
415 isc_mutex_destroy(&cd->lock);
416
417 mctx = cd->mctx;
418 isc_mem_put(mctx, cd, sizeof(*cd));
419 isc_mem_destroy(&mctx);
420}

422/*
423 * Called to start a transaction
424 */
425static isc_result_t
426dlopen_dlz_newversion(const char *zone, void *driverarg, void *dbdata,
427 void **versionp)
428{
429 dlopen_data_t *cd = (dlopen_data_t *) dbdata;
430 isc_result_t result;
431
432 UNUSED(driverarg);
433
434 if (cd->dlz_newversion == NULL)
435 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
436
437 MAYBE_LOCK(cd);
438 result = cd->dlz_newversion(zone, cd->dbdata, versionp);
439 MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd);
440 return (result);
441}
442
443/*
444 * Called to end a transaction
445 */
446static void
447dlopen_dlz_closeversion(const char *zone, bool commit,
448 void *driverarg, void *dbdata, void **versionp)
449{
450 dlopen_data_t *cd = (dlopen_data_t *) dbdata;
451
452 UNUSED(driverarg);
453
454 if (cd->dlz_newversion == NULL) {
455 *versionp = NULL;
456 return;
457 }
458
459 MAYBE_LOCK(cd);
460 cd->dlz_closeversion(zone, commit, cd->dbdata, versionp);
461 MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd);
462}

464/*
465 * Called on startup to configure any writeable zones
466 */
467static isc_result_t
468dlopen_dlz_configure(dns_view_t *view, dns_dlzdb_t *dlzdb,
469 void *driverarg, void *dbdata)
470{
471 dlopen_data_t *cd = (dlopen_data_t *) dbdata;
472 isc_result_t result;
473
474 UNUSED(driverarg);
475
476 if (cd->dlz_configure == NULL)
477 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
478
479 MAYBE_LOCK(cd);
480 cd->in_configure = true;
481 result = cd->dlz_configure(view, dlzdb, cd->dbdata);
482 cd->in_configure = false;
483 MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd);
484
485 return (result);
486}

489/*
490 * Check for authority to change a name.
491 */
492static bool
493dlopen_dlz_ssumatch(const char *signer, const char *name, const char *tcpaddr,
494 const char *type, const char *key, uint32_t keydatalen,
495 unsigned char *keydata, void *driverarg, void *dbdata)
496{
497 dlopen_data_t *cd = (dlopen_data_t *) dbdata;
498 bool ret;
499
500 UNUSED(driverarg);
501
502 if (cd->dlz_ssumatch == NULL)
503 return (false);
504
505 MAYBE_LOCK(cd);
506 ret = cd->dlz_ssumatch(signer, name, tcpaddr, type, key, keydatalen,
507 keydata, cd->dbdata);
508 MAYBE_UNLOCK(cd);
509
510 return (ret);
511}

599/*
600 * Register driver with BIND
601 */
602isc_result_t
603dlz_dlopen_init(isc_mem_t *mctx) {
604#ifndef ISC_DLZ_DLOPEN
605 UNUSED(mctx);
606 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
607#else
608 isc_result_t result;
609
610 dlopen_log(2, "Registering DLZ_dlopen driver");
611
612 result = dns_sdlzregister("dlopen", &dlz_dlopen_methods, NULL,
613 DNS_SDLZFLAG_RELATIVEOWNER |
614 DNS_SDLZFLAG_RELATIVERDATA |
615 DNS_SDLZFLAG_THREADSAFE,
616 mctx, &dlz_dlopen);
617
618 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
619 UNEXPECTED_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
620 "dns_sdlzregister() failed: %s",
621 isc_result_totext(result));
622 result = ISC_R_UNEXPECTED;
623 }
624
625 return (result);
626#endif
627}

630/*
631 * Unregister the driver
632 */
633void
634dlz_dlopen_clear(void) {
635#ifdef ISC_DLZ_DLOPEN
636 dlopen_log(2, "Unregistering DLZ_dlopen driver");
637 if (dlz_dlopen != NULL)
638 dns_sdlzunregister(&dlz_dlopen);
639#endif
